  "prompt": "I have been working out for almost a year now. My strength is increased but I am hardly building any muscle. What should I do to increase my muscle size?",
  "response": "To increase muscle size (hypertrophy), consider these strategies:\n\n1. Nutrition\n- Increase protein intake (1.6-2.2g per kg of body weight)\n- Eat in a slight caloric surplus\n- Consume balanced meals with adequate carbs and healthy fats\n- Stay hydrated\n\n2. Training Techniques\n- Focus on progressive overload\n- Use compound exercises (squats, deadlifts, bench press)\n- Perform 3-4 sets of 8-12 repetitions\n- Vary your workout routine\n- Include isolation exercises\n- Minimize cardio to prevent muscle breakdown\n\n3. Rest and Recovery\n- Get 7-9 hours of sleep\n- Allow muscle groups 48-72 hours of rest between workouts\n- Consider proper post-workout nutrition\n\n4. Supplementation (optional)\n- Protein powder\n- Creatine\n- Branched-chain amino acids (BCAAs)\n\n5. Training Intensity\n- Lift heavier weights\n- Reduce rest time between sets\n- Use techniques like drop sets and supersets\n\n6. Hormonal Considerations\n- Manage stress levels\n- Get testosterone levels checked\n- Ensure adequate sleep\n\nConsult a fitness professional or nutritionist for personalized advice tailored to your specific needs and body type.",
